=== Prognosis Data

Long-term follow-up studies demonstrate substantially better outcomes in pediatric ME/CFS than adult disease @Rowe2019pediatric:

    - *Recovery at 5 years*: 38%
    - *Recovery at 10 years*: 68%
    - *Overall improvement or recovery*: 54–94% across studies
    - *Mean illness duration*: 5 years (range 1–15 years)
    - *Functional status at 10-year follow-up*: Mean 8/10
    - *Proportion still very unwell*: Only 5% with function $<$6/10 at 10 years
    - *Working or studying full-time*: 63% at follow-up

These figures include children who were severely affected. The data demonstrate that even severe pediatric ME/CFS is not necessarily permanent.

